OL,3,GNorthern Ireland
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FRain near the east coast will
OL,6,Fquickly clear away. Otherwise it will
OL,7,Fbe a mainly dry morning with sunny
OL,8,Fspells. Turning cloudier in the
OL,9,Fafternoon with odd shower around and a
OL,10,Ffreshening southwesterly breeze.
OL,11,
OL,12,CTonight:FA mostly cloudy evening with
OL,13,Fa few showers moving eastwards.
OL,14,FBecoming dry with clear spells
OL,15,Fovernight leading to a frost in places.
OL,16,
OL,17,CTuesday:FA cold start to the day with
OL,18,Fa frost for some places. It will
OL,19,Fremain dry with plenty of sunshine but
OL,20,Fperhaps some high cloud spreading east
OL,21,Fin the afternoon.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
